
[1]foliated

   FO'LIATED, pp.

   1. Spread or covered with a thin plate or foil.

   2. In mineralogy, consisting of plates; resembling or in the form of a
   plate; lamellar; as a foliated fracture.

   Minerals that consist of grains, and are at the same time foliated, are
   called granularly foliated.
